    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-09-06</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-11-19T22:43:59Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Camera Phone Predator Alert Act - Requires any mobile phone containing a digital camera to sound a tone whenever a photograph is taken with the camera's phone. Prohibits such a phone from being equipped with a means of disabling or silencing the tone. Treats the requirement as a consumer product safety standard and requires enforcement by the Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC).</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Camera Phone Predator Alert Act</title>
    <titles>
